---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Webtracker Chrome Extension | jmfernxndez"
  description="Track your website time with Webtracker, a lightweight Chrome extension by jmfernxndez. 100% offline, private, and perfect for freelancers and remote workers!"
>
  <div class="container">
    <h1>Webtracker: Private Website Time Tracking by jmfernxndez</h1>

    <section class="intro">
      <p>
        <strong>Webtracker</strong> is a lightweight Chrome extension designed to
        help you track the time you spend on websites—completely offline. Built by
        <a href="https://github.com/jmfernxndez" target="_blank">jmfernxndez</a
        >, this privacy-first tool keeps all data on your device, making it
        ideal for freelancers, remote workers, and anyone looking to boost
        productivity.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="features">
      <h2>Why Choose Webtracker?</h2>
      <p>
        Webtracker empowers you to monitor your browsing habits without
        compromising privacy. Its minimalist design and powerful features make
        it a must-have for productivity enthusiasts. Key features include:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Time Tracking</strong>: Measure time spent on active browser
          tabs, with per-domain breakdowns.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>100% Offline</strong>: No cloud, no sync, no external
          tracking—your data stays local.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Lightweight</strong>: At just 84.2KiB, it runs smoothly
          without slowing your browser.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Easy to Use</strong>: Install and start tracking instantly, no
          configuration needed.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Explore the source code on <a
          href="https://github.com/jmfernxndez/webtracker"
          target="_blank">GitHub</a
        > or install it from the <a
          href="https://chromewebstore.google.com/detail/webtracker/npjlldagpoffopoebglliclamgemddgh"
          target="_blank">Chrome Web Store</a
        >.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="why-me">
      <h2>Built by jmfernxndez, Freelance Web Developer</h2>
      <p>
        As a passionate freelance web developer, I (jmfernxndez) created
        Webtracker to help professionals like you stay productive while
        prioritizing privacy. With my expertise in JavaScript and Chrome
        extension development, I’ve crafted a tool that’s:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Reliable</strong>: Built with modern web technologies for
          seamless performance.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Private</strong>: No data collection, ensuring your browsing
          habits stay yours.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Open-Source</strong>: Contribute or review the code on <a
            href="https://github.com/jmfernxndez/webtracker"
            target="_blank">GitHub</a
          >.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Have questions or suggestions? Reach out to me at <a
          href="mailto:jmfernandez@vantag.es">jmfernandez@vantag.es</a
        >.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="cta">
      <h2>Start Tracking Your Time Today</h2>
      <p>
        Ready to take control of your productivity? Install Webtracker now from
        the <a
          href="https://chromewebstore.google.com/detail/webtracker/npjlldagpoffopoebglliclamgemddgh"
          target="_blank">Chrome Web Store</a
        > or <a href="/contact">contact me</a> for custom web development solutions.
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>

  <style>
    .container {
      max-width: 800px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 2rem;
      font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
    }
    h1 {
      font-size: 2.5rem;
      color: #1a1a1a;
      text-align: center;
      margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    }
    h2 {
      font-size: 1.8rem;
      color: #333;
      margin-top: 2rem;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }
    p {
      line-height: 1.6;
      color: #555;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }
    ul {
      list-style-type: disc;
      margin-left: 2rem;
      margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    }
    li {
      margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
      color: #555;
    }
    a {
      color: #007bff;
      text-decoration: none;
    }
    a:hover {
      text-decoration: underline;
    }
    .cta {
      text-align: center;
      padding: 2rem 0;
    }
  </style></Layout
>
